  "intent": "Execute an automated immunofluorescence slide staining protocol with sequential reagent addition and PBS washes. Add 100\u00b5L blocking reagent to slide wells, incubate 1 hour at 4\u00b0C, add 100\u00b5L primary antibody with 1-hour incubation, perform 4mL PBS wash with moving dispense across well diameter, add 100\u00b5L secondary antibody with 1-hour incubation, wash with 4mL PBS, add 100\u00b5L nuclear counterstain with 5-minute incubation, and perform final 4mL PBS wash. Protocol accommodates 1-8 slide blocks with customizable reagent volumes and tip reuse options.",
